<m0>(box) GUYANA <m0>(--) The Finance Ministry says a bill recently introduced in Parliament will modernize Guyana's currency exchange regulations and bring them in line with other Caribbean countries. <ql>
<m0>(box) DOMINICA <m0>(--) The government is putting tougher measures in place to deal with a growing problem of crops being stolen from farmers, Prime Minister Edison James said.<ql>
<m0>(box) JAMAICA <m0>(--) Col. Trevor Macmillan, appointed police commissioner in 1993 for three years, will remain in the post for two more years, Prime Minister P.J. Patterson told the House of Representatives this week. <ql>
<m0>(box) BARBADOS <m0>(--) Revelers took to the streets of Bridgetown on Wednesday for a street parade climaxing the two-week Congaline Carnival, now in its third year, sponsored by a local manufacturer of rum-based products in conjunction with the National Cultural Foundation.<ql>
